title: AttributeError: module 'torch.jit' has no attribute '_script_if_tracing'
body:
## ❔Question
After installing requirements with conda, I get this error trying to run detect.py.

I've tested just do `import torchvision` and the exactly same error appear.
Are you all shure that torchvision's version 0.7.0 is stable?

## Additional context

> Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<stdin>", line 1, in <module>
  File "/home/joabe/anaconda3/envs/mosca_env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torchvision/__init__.py", line 5, in <module>
    from torchvision import models
  File "/home/joabe/anaconda3/envs/mosca_env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torchvision/models/__init__.py", line 12, in <module>
    from . import detection
  File "/home/joabe/anaconda3/envs/mosca_env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torchvision/models/detection/__init__.py", line 1, in <module>
    from .faster_rcnn import *
  File "/home/joabe/anaconda3/envs/mosca_env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torchvision/models/detection/faster_rcnn.py", line 7, in <module>
    from torchvision.ops import misc as misc_nn_ops
  File "/home/joabe/anaconda3/envs/mosca_env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torchvision/ops/__init__.py", line 1, in <module>
    from .boxes import nms, box_iou
  File "/home/joabe/anaconda3/envs/mosca_env/lib/python3.7/site-packages/torchvision/ops/boxes.py", line 43, in <module>
    @torch.jit._script_if_tracing
AttributeError: module 'torch.jit' has no attribute '_script_if_tracing'
